<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79a06639-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1676"><num value="1676">§ 1676.</num><heading> Enforcement by Secretary of Labor</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Labor, acting through the Wage and Hour Division of the Department of Labor, shall enforce the provisions of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id79a0663a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/321/tIII/s306">Pub. L. 90–321, title III, § 306</ref>, <date date="1968-05-29">May 29, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/164">82 Stat. 164</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
